This data is part of a pre-publication release. For information on the proper use of pre-publication data shared by the Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute (including details of any publication moratoria)%2C please see http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sanger.ac.uk%2Fdatasharing%2F%0A. Zoonotic infections from animals to humans represent a significant proportion of global emerging infectious diseases.  This study aims to characterise all viruses present in samples from species with a high risk of transmission of zoonotic infections. Samples from bats will be sequenced on the Illumina platform to obtain a large sequencing data set which can be used to identify novel pathogens with zoonotic potential.
